		{"id":"af4dc040834d3d70","type":"text","text":"\n| Category                                     | Core Focus                             | What It Covers                                                                                                                                                               |\n| -------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| **Technical Skills & Craft**                 | How you think and build as an engineer | Hands-on work with code, systems, tools, architectures, patterns, trade-offs, debugging, and design decisions that reflect your technical depth and problem-solving ability. |\n| **Projects & Execution**                     | Proof of applied ability               | What you have built, shipped, experimented with, broken, fixed, or improved—evidence that you can apply knowledge and execute beyond theory.                                 |\n| **Professional Growth & Industry Awareness** | How you operate in the real world      | Understanding teamwork, communication, roles, expectations, career navigation, and how software development works within organizations and the broader industry.             |\n| **Mindset, Values & Professional Identity**  | Who you are becoming                   | Communication, discipline, resilience, ethics, consistency, and long-term thinking—the traits that shape a reliable, trustworthy professional, not just a skilled one.       |\n","x":-638,"y":-1220,"width":1245,"height":380}
